hm2DhcpsMib.name: hm2DhcpsMib

hm2DhcpsMib.description: Hirschmann DHCP server MIB. Copyright (C) 2012. All Rights Reserved.

hm2DHCPServerMode.name: hm2DHCPServerMode
hm2DHCPServerMode.description: Enable or disable DHCP server global.

hm2DHCPServerPoolTable.name: hm2DHCPServerPoolTable
hm2DHCPServerPoolTable.description: A table containing the DHCP server pools.

hm2DHCPServerPoolEntry.name: hm2DHCPServerPoolEntry
hm2DHCPServerPoolEntry.description: A logical row in the hm2DHCPServerPoolTable.

hm2DHCPServerPoolStartIpAddress.name: hm2DHCPServerPoolStartIpAddress
hm2DHCPServerPoolStartIpAddress.description: The IPv4 address of the first address in the range. The value of hm2DHCPServerPoolStartIpAddress MUST be less than or equal to the value of hm2DHCPServerPoolEndIpAddress.

hm2DHCPServerPoolEndIpAddress.name: hm2DHCPServerPoolEndIpAddress
hm2DHCPServerPoolEndIpAddress.description: The IPv4 address of the last address in the range. The value of hm2DHCPServerPoolEndIpAddress MUST be greater than or equal to the value of hm2DHCPServerPoolStartIpAddress.

hm2DHCPServerPoolLeaseTime.name: hm2DHCPServerPoolLeaseTime
hm2DHCPServerPoolLeaseTime.description: The pools lease time in number of seconds. A value of 4294967295 SHOULD be used for leases that have a lease time which is 'infinite' and for BOOTP leases.

hm2DHCPServerPoolFlags.name: hm2DHCPServerPoolFlags
hm2DHCPServerPoolFlags.description: This object shows the parameters that are used to lease the IP Address.

hm2DHCPServerPoolMacAddress.name: hm2DHCPServerPoolMacAddress
hm2DHCPServerPoolMacAddress.description: The MAC Address of the entry that is used to lease the IP Address.

hm2DHCPServerPoolGateway.name: hm2DHCPServerPoolGateway
hm2DHCPServerPoolGateway.description: The IPv4 address of the Gatewayinterface that is used to lease the IP Address.

hm2DHCPServerPoolClientId.name: hm2DHCPServerPoolClientId
hm2DHCPServerPoolClientId.description: The Client Identifier of the entry that is used to lease the IP Address.

hm2DHCPServerPoolRemoteId.name: hm2DHCPServerPoolRemoteId
hm2DHCPServerPoolRemoteId.description: The Remote Identifier of the entry that is used to lease the IP Address. The Remote Identifier must be send in Option 82 as defined in RFC 3046.

hm2DHCPServerPoolCircuitId.name: hm2DHCPServerPoolCircuitId
hm2DHCPServerPoolCircuitId.description: The Cicuit Identifier of the entry that is used to lease the IP Address. The Circuit Identifier must be send in Option 82 as defined in RFC 3046.

hm2DHCPServerPoolVlanId.name: hm2DHCPServerPoolVlanId
hm2DHCPServerPoolVlanId.description: The Vlan ID of the entry that is used to lease the IP Address. A value of -1 corresponds to management vlan (the default), any other value (1-4042) represents a specific VLAN

hm2DHCPServerPoolOptionConfFileName.name: hm2DHCPServerPoolOptionConfFileName
hm2DHCPServerPoolOptionConfFileName.description: Full specified name of the configuration file e.g. tftp://192.9.200.1/cfg/config1.sav. An empty string zeros the SNAME and the FILE field in the DHCP header.

hm2DHCPServerPoolOptionGateway.name: hm2DHCPServerPoolOptionGateway
hm2DHCPServerPoolOptionGateway.description: The IPv4 address of the Gateway. A value of 0 disables the attachment of the option field in the DHCP message.

hm2DHCPServerPoolOptionNetmask.name: hm2DHCPServerPoolOptionNetmask
hm2DHCPServerPoolOptionNetmask.description: The subnet mask. A value of 0 disables the attachment of the option field in the DHCP message.

hm2DHCPServerPoolOptionWINS.name: hm2DHCPServerPoolOptionWINS
hm2DHCPServerPoolOptionWINS.description: The IPv4 address of the WINS Server. A value of 0 disables the attachment of the option field in the DHCP message.

hm2DHCPServerPoolOptionDNS.name: hm2DHCPServerPoolOptionDNS
hm2DHCPServerPoolOptionDNS.description: The IPv4 address of the DNS Server. A value of 0 disables the attachment of the option field in the DHCP message.

hm2DHCPServerPoolOptionHostname.name: hm2DHCPServerPoolOptionHostname
hm2DHCPServerPoolOptionHostname.description: The name of the client (Option 12). An empty string disables the attachment of the option field in the DHCP message.

hm2DHCPServerPoolMethod.name: hm2DHCPServerPoolMethod
hm2DHCPServerPoolMethod.description: The source of the DHCP Server Pool. User can set the object to none(1), config(2), ttdp(3).

hm2DHCPServerPoolErrorStatus.name: hm2DHCPServerPoolErrorStatus
hm2DHCPServerPoolErrorStatus.description: The error Code by create a new Pool.

hm2DHCPServerPoolRowStatus.name: hm2DHCPServerPoolRowStatus
hm2DHCPServerPoolRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

hm2DHCPServerLeaseTable.name: hm2DHCPServerLeaseTable
hm2DHCPServerLeaseTable.description: A table containing the DHCP server leases.

hm2DHCPServerLeaseEntry.name: hm2DHCPServerLeaseEntry
hm2DHCPServerLeaseEntry.description: A logical row in the hm2DHCPServerLeaseTable.

hm2DHCPServerLeasePoolIndex.name: hm2DHCPServerLeasePoolIndex
hm2DHCPServerLeasePoolIndex.description: The index of the hm2DHCPServerPoolTable above.

hm2DHCPServerLeaseIpAddress.name: hm2DHCPServerLeaseIpAddress
hm2DHCPServerLeaseIpAddress.description: This is an IP address from the pool with index hm2DHCPServerLeasePoolIndex.

hm2DHCPServerLeaseTimeRemaining.name: hm2DHCPServerLeaseTimeRemaining
hm2DHCPServerLeaseTimeRemaining.description: The remaining time of the lease configured in hm2DHCPServerPoolLeaseTime.

hm2DHCPServerLeaseIfIndex.name: hm2DHCPServerLeaseIfIndex
hm2DHCPServerLeaseIfIndex.description: The interface index where the lease is currently active.

hm2DHCPServerLeaseClientMacAddress.name: hm2DHCPServerLeaseClientMacAddress
hm2DHCPServerLeaseClientMacAddress.description: The MAC Address of the entry that has leased the IP Address.

hm2DHCPServerLeaseGateway.name: hm2DHCPServerLeaseGateway
hm2DHCPServerLeaseGateway.description: The IPv4 address of the Gatewayinterface that was used to lease the IP Address.

hm2DHCPServerLeaseClientId.name: hm2DHCPServerLeaseClientId
hm2DHCPServerLeaseClientId.description: The Client Identifier of the entry that was used to lease the IP Address.

hm2DHCPServerLeaseRemoteId.name: hm2DHCPServerLeaseRemoteId
hm2DHCPServerLeaseRemoteId.description: The Remote Identifier of the entry that was used to lease the IP Address.

hm2DHCPServerLeaseCircuitId.name: hm2DHCPServerLeaseCircuitId
hm2DHCPServerLeaseCircuitId.description: The Cicuit Identifier of the entry that was used to lease the IP Address.

hm2DHCPServerLeaseAction.name: hm2DHCPServerLeaseAction
hm2DHCPServerLeaseAction.description: Manually release this ip address for new assignment.

hm2DHCPServerLeaseVlanId.name: hm2DHCPServerLeaseVlanId
hm2DHCPServerLeaseVlanId.description: The Vlan ID of the entry that is used to lease the IP Address. A value of -1 corresponds to management vlan (the default), any other value (1-4042) represents a specific VLAN

hm2DHCPServerIfConfigTable.name: hm2DHCPServerIfConfigTable
hm2DHCPServerIfConfigTable.description: A table containing current configuration information for each interface.

hm2DHCPServerIfConfigEntry.name: hm2DHCPServerIfConfigEntry
hm2DHCPServerIfConfigEntry.description: A logical row in the hm2DHCPServerIfConfigTable.

hm2DHCPServerIfConfigMode.name: hm2DHCPServerIfConfigMode
hm2DHCPServerIfConfigMode.description: Enable or disable DHCP server on this interface.

hm2DHCPServerCounterIfTable.name: hm2DHCPServerCounterIfTable
hm2DHCPServerCounterIfTable.description: A table containing current configuration information for each interface.

hm2DHCPServerCounterIfEntry.name: hm2DHCPServerCounterIfEntry
hm2DHCPServerCounterIfEntry.description: A logical row in the hm2DHCPServerCounterIfTable.

hm2DHCPServerCounterBootpRequests.name: hm2DHCPServerCounterBootpRequests
hm2DHCPServerCounterBootpRequests.description: The number of packets received that contain a Message Type of 1 (BOOTREQUEST) in the first octet and do not contain option number 53 (DHCP Message Type) in the options.

hm2DHCPServerCounterBootpInvalids.name: hm2DHCPServerCounterBootpInvalids
hm2DHCPServerCounterBootpInvalids.description: The number of packets received that do not contain a Message Type of 1 (BOOTREQUEST) in the first octet or are not valid BOOTP packets (e.g., too short, invalid field in packet header).

hm2DHCPServerCounterBootpReplies.name: hm2DHCPServerCounterBootpReplies
hm2DHCPServerCounterBootpReplies.description: The number of packets sent that contain a Message Type of 2 (BOOTREPLY) in the first octet and do not contain option number 53 (DHCP Message Type) in the options.

hm2DHCPServerCounterBootpDroppedUnknownC.name: hm2DHCPServerCounterBootpDroppedUnknownClients
hm2DHCPServerCounterBootpDroppedUnknownC.description: The number of BOOTP packets dropped due to the server not recognizing or not providing service to the hardware address received in the incoming packet.

hm2DHCPServerCounterBootpDroppedNotServi.name: hm2DHCPServerCounterBootpDroppedNotServingSubnet
hm2DHCPServerCounterBootpDroppedNotServi.description: The number of BOOTP packets dropped due to the server not being configured or not otherwise able to serve addresses on the subnet from which this message was received.

hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4Discovers.name: hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4Discovers
hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4Discovers.description: The number of DHCPDISCOVER (option 53 with value 1) packets received.

hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4Offers.name: hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4Offers
hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4Offers.description: The number of DHCPOFFER (option 53 with value 2) packets sent.

hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4Requests.name: hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4Requests
hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4Requests.description: The number of DHCPREQUEST (option 53 with value 3) packets received.

hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4Declines.name: hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4Declines
hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4Declines.description: The number of DHCPDECLINE (option 53 with value 4) packets received.

hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4Acks.name: hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4Acks
hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4Acks.description: The number of DHCPACK (option 53 with value 5) packets sent.

hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4Naks.name: hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4Naks
hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4Naks.description: The number of DHCPNACK (option 53 with value 6) packets sent.

hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4Releases.name: hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4Releases
hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4Releases.description: The number of DHCPRELEASE (option 53 with value 7) packets received.

hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4Informs.name: hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4Informs
hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4Informs.description: The number of DHCPINFORM (option 53 with value 8) packets received.

hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4ForcedRenews.name: hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4ForcedRenews
hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4ForcedRenews.description: The number of DHCPFORCERENEW (option 53 with value 9) packets sent.

hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4Invalids.name: hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4Invalids
hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4Invalids.description: The number of DHCP packets received whose DHCP message type (i.e., option number 53) is not understood or handled by the server.

hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4DroppedUnknown.name: hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4DroppedUnknownClient
hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4DroppedUnknown.description: The number of DHCP packets dropped due to the server not recognizing or not providing service to the client-id and/or hardware address received in the incoming packet.

hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4DroppedNotServ.name: hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4DroppedNotServingSubnet
hm2DHCPServerCounterDhcpv4DroppedNotServ.description: The number of DHCP packets dropped due to the server not being configured or not otherwise able to serve addresses on the subnet from which this message was received.

hm2DHCPServerCounterMiscOtherDhcpServer.name: hm2DHCPServerCounterMiscOtherDhcpServer
hm2DHCPServerCounterMiscOtherDhcpServer.description: The number of BOOTP and DHCP packets from another DHCP server seen on this interface.

hm2DHCPServerRowStatusInvalidConfigurati.name: hm2DHCPServerRowStatusInvalidConfigurationErrorReturn
hm2DHCPServerRowStatusInvalidConfigurati.description: DHCP Server pool with index {0} cannot be enabled, errors in data entry.

hm2DHCPServerConflictDHCPRrelayErrorRetu.name: hm2DHCPServerConflictDHCPRrelayErrorReturn
hm2DHCPServerConflictDHCPRrelayErrorRetu.description: {0} and {1} cannot be active at the same time.
